video.title: JoJo's Bizarre Adventure
video.synopsis: Multiple generations of the Joestar family -- all with the same nickname -- confront supernatural villains through a series of time periods.

episodes.synopsis: When Dio Brando joins an aristocratic family upon his father’s death, he secretly swears to take everything from their heir Jonathan “JoJo” Joestar.
episodes.title: Dio The Invader

episodes.synopsis: JoJo meets a street gang boss named Speedwagon when he goes to London to investigate the suspected poisoning of his father by Dio.
episodes.title: A Letter From the Past

episodes.synopsis: When JoJo confronts Dio after giving his father the antidote, Dio attacks JoJo with a knife and uses the bloodied stone mask on himself.
episodes.title: Youth with Dio

episodes.synopsis: JoJo is reunited with his first love, Erina. A man named Will A. Zeppeli demonstrates his strange power and tells JoJo he must destroy the stone mask.
episodes.title: Overdrive

episodes.synopsis: JoJo and his companions are ambushed by Dio and a horde of zombies after a boy named Poco lures them into a graveyard.
episodes.title: The Dark Knights

episodes.synopsis: The resurrected legendary knight Bruford regains his human soul and entrusts JoJo with his sword; Tarkus attacks JoJo with his overwhelming power.
episodes.title: Tomorrow's Courage

episodes.synopsis: Zeppeli takes on Tarkus despite knowing his grim fate. In his final act, he uses his remaining strength to pass on his powers to his successor JoJo.
episodes.title: Sorrowful Successor

episodes.synopsis: JoJo rescues Poco’s sister, but Zeppeli’s friend Dire is completely obliterated by Dio. With Bruford’s sword in hand, JoJo faces Dio once again.
episodes.title: Bloody Battle! JoJo & Dio

episodes.synopsis: JoJo and Erina embark on a honeymoon cruise after their wedding. But to JoJo’s utter shock, one of Dio’s servants appears aboard the ship.
episodes.title: The Final Ripple!

episodes.synopsis: Many stone masks are discovered at a Mexican ruin in 1938. Meanwhile in New York, JoJo’s grandson Joseph helps a young man named Smokey.
episodes.title: New York's JoJo

episodes.synopsis: Joseph fights against Straizo, who became a vampire after betraying his friend Speedwagon. After the battle, Straizo warns about “the Pillar Man.”
episodes.title: The Game Master

episodes.synopsis: Joseph gets attacked by one of Stroheim’s men after arriving in Mexico. Meanwhile, Stroheim attempts to awaken the Pillar Man Santana.
episodes.title: The Pillar Man

episodes.synopsis: Joseph uses his Ripple power to escape after being absorbed into Santana’s body. When that fails, he tries exposing Santana to sunlight.
episodes.title: JoJo vs. The Ultimate Lifeform

episodes.synopsis: Joseph and Speedwagon meet Zeppeli’s grandson Caesar when they arrive in Rome after learning about the other Pillar Men.
episodes.title: Ultimate Warriors from Ancient Times

episodes.synopsis: Wamuu the Pillar Man easily nullifies Caesar Zeppeli’s Bubble Launcher attack and injures him; Joseph reveals his newly developed secret technique.
episodes.title: A Hero's Proof

episodes.synopsis: Caesar takes Joseph to Venice and introduces him to his mentor Lisa Lisa, who starts rigorously training him how to control his Ripple powers.
episodes.title: Lisa Lisa, Hamon Coach

episodes.synopsis: Lisa Lisa tells Joseph that the gem known as the “Super Aja” is required to destroy the Pillar Men; Joseph and Caesar take on other Ripple masters.
episodes.title: The Deeper Plan

episodes.synopsis: Joseph and Caesar combine their Ripple powers to deal with the Pillar Man who took over Suzi Q’s body to steal the Red Stone of Aja.
episodes.title: Von Stroheim's Revenge

episodes.synopsis: Stroheim begins fighting Kars in his new mechanical body. Meanwhile, Joseph and Kars fall off a cliff during their attempt to get the Red Stone.
episodes.title: A Race Toward the Blink

episodes.synopsis: Caesar arrives at the enemy’s hideout with a new attack move up his sleeve as Lisa Lisa reveals his past to Joseph.
episodes.title: Young Caesar

episodes.synopsis: Lisa Lisa comes up with a clever plan when she and Joseph find Wamuu and Kars waiting for them at the hotel with a hundred of their vampire minions.
episodes.title: A Hundred Against Two

episodes.synopsis: Joseph and Wamuu begin their deadly chariot race at an ancient arena. Despite grabbing the first weapon, Joseph finds himself in a perilous situation.
episodes.title: A True Warrior

episodes.synopsis: Joseph counters Wamuu’s final attack with Caesar’s flaming bandanna. Lisa Lisa challenges Kars to one-on-one combat at the temple ruins.
episodes.title: The Warrior Of Wind

episodes.synopsis: Joseph struggles to prevent Lisa Lisa from falling to her death. In the aftermath, Speedwagon reveals the details of Lisa Lisa’s past.
episodes.title: The Ties that Bind JoJo

episodes.synopsis: The Red Stone makes Kars virtually invincible. Joseph heads toward a volcano on a plane to lure Kars to his fiery doom.
episodes.title: The Birth of a Superbeing

episodes.synopsis: Kars emerges from the molten lava and slices Joseph’s arm off. Joseph instinctively holds the Red Stone up to receive the finishing blow from Kars.
episodes.title: The Ascendant One

episodes.synopsis: 1987. Joseph travels to Japan after hearing that his grandson Jotaro claims to be possessed by evil spirits and refuses to leave his holding cell.
episodes.title: A Man Possessed by an Evil Spirit

episodes.synopsis: Jotaro hides what Joseph calls a “Stand” as he returns to his normal life. When Jotaro is hurt on his way to school, he meets a student named Kakyoin.
episodes.title: Who Will Be the Judge!?

episodes.synopsis: Jotaro ignores Joseph’s protestations and tries to use his Stand to remove the mind controller DIO implanted into Kakyoin’s brain.
episodes.title: The Curse of Dio

episodes.synopsis: Kakyoin takes action against a Stand without knowing who its user is as Jotaro and his crew encounter one of DIO’s assassins on the plane to Egypt.
episodes.title: Tower of Gray

episodes.synopsis: Victory seems all but certain as Avdol attacks DIO’s mind-controlled assassin Polnareff with his flame wielding abilities.
episodes.title: Silver Chariot

episodes.synopsis: Jotaro and his crew head to Singapore by sea; a Stand with an unknown user attacks Jotaro soon after a stowaway is discovered aboard the ship.
episodes.title: Dark Blue Moon

episodes.synopsis: Jotaro’s group comes across a freighter that seems abandoned but for one orangutan. As they search the ship, the ship’s crane suddenly starts to move.
episodes.title: Strength

episodes.synopsis: Jotaro’s group arrive at their hotel in Singapore, but Polnareff falls right into a Stand user’s trap when he gets to his room.
episodes.title: Devil

episodes.synopsis: Jotaro starts to suspect that Kakyoin must be possessed when he sees him acting strange and brutally beating up a thief while exploring Singapore.
episodes.title: Yellow Temperance

episodes.synopsis: Polnareff heads off on his own to avenge his sister after he is attacked by a strange Stand that he can only see in a mirror’s reflection.
episodes.title: The Emperor and the Hanged Man, Part 1

episodes.synopsis: Kakyoin tries to convince Polnareff to run away when he determines that his ally is fighting a losing battle against the enemy Stand.
episodes.title: The Emperor and the Hanged Man, Part 2

episodes.synopsis: A strange bump on Joseph's arm keeps getting bigger. When a doctor tries to excise it, a face appears on the growth and declares itself a Stand.
episodes.title: The Empress

episodes.synopsis: Jotaro and his crew come across another car as they drive through a mountain road; Polnareff passes it and drives straight into an oncoming truck.
episodes.title: Wheel of Fortune

episodes.synopsis: Jotaro and his crew suspect that a Stand is nearby when they discover a horrific corpse in a strangely quiet Pakistani town.
episodes.title: Justice, Part 1

episodes.synopsis: Polnareff gets attacked by an army of reanimated corpses when he realizes that the old woman who runs the hotel is a Stand user.
episodes.title: Justice, Part 2

episodes.synopsis: Jotaro and his crew enter a battle with a ruthless assassin who follows DIO’s orders to kill his comrade without hesitation.
episodes.title: The Lovers, Part 1

episodes.synopsis: Kakyoin and Polnareff discover an enemy Stand capable of wreaking havoc on brain cells when they send their Stands into Joseph’s head.
episodes.title: The Lovers, Part 2

episodes.synopsis: Jotaro and his crew travel through a desert where the suspicious looking sun doesn’t set and the temperature rises to blistering levels.
episodes.title: The Sun

episodes.synopsis: Kakyoin has a dream of an amusement park where a baby’s cries can be heard. Back in the real world, a baby passenger joins Jotaro’s crew on a plane.
episodes.title: Death 13, Part 1

episodes.synopsis: No one takes Kakyoin’s concerns about the baby seriously, but Jotaro and the others soon realize the truth when they find themselves in a dream world.
episodes.title: Death 13, Part 2

episodes.synopsis: Jotaro and his crew meet Avdol’s father on a remote island, but the man shuts himself up in his house. Meanwhile, Polnareff discovers a strange lamp.
episodes.title: Judgement, Part 1

episodes.synopsis: The enemy Stand that emerged from the lamp resurrects Avdol with Polnareff’s third wish, but the once-dead only seem to want Polnareff dead.
episodes.title: Judgement, Part 2

episodes.synopsis: Jotaro and his crew head for Egypt on a submarine to confront DIO, but a coffee mug suddenly goes through a transformation as they near the continent.
episodes.title: High Priestess, Part 1

episodes.synopsis: Jotaro and his crew find what looks to be two undersea tunnels after evacuating their submarine to get away from the shapeshifting enemy Stand.
episodes.title: High Priestess, Part 2

episodes.synopsis: A helicopter lands in front of Jotaro and his crew when they arrive in Egypt, but the helper Joseph requested doesn’t appear to be on the aircraft.
episodes.title: Iggy the Fool and Geb's N'Doul, Part 1

episodes.synopsis: Avdol devises a plan to counter the water Stand’s attacks, but the enemy figures it out. Meanwhile, their helper Iggy falls asleep during the fight.
episodes.title: Iggy the Fool and Geb's N'Doul, Part 2

episodes.synopsis: Kakyoin and Avdol seek medical treatment as the remaining men unknowingly walk into a café where two Stand-using brothers await.
episodes.title: Khnum's Oingo and Thoth's Boingo

episodes.synopsis: A young man named Chaka suddenly changes his personality after he finds a mysterious sword. Meanwhile, Jotaro and his crew make their way to Cairo.
episodes.title: Anubis, Part 1

episodes.synopsis: Polnareff realizes that Chaka’s sword itself is a Stand when he is attacked by his barber, but the sword has grown stronger since their last fight.
episodes.title: Anubis, Part 2

episodes.synopsis: Joseph gets shocked by touching a strange rock embedded with an electrical outlet when Jotaro and his crew arrive at the city of Luxor.
episodes.title: Bastet's Mariah, Part 1

episodes.synopsis: Joseph and Avdol get stuck together thanks to the enemy Stand. When they finally manage to separate, their feet get stuck on a railroad track.
episodes.title: Bastet's Mariah, Part 2

episodes.synopsis: Polnareff suddenly notices that his shoes are several sizes too big after unsuccessfully giving chase to a man who was following him.
episodes.title: Set's Alessi, Part 1

episodes.synopsis: Polnareff must fight the Stand user Alessi in his juvenile state with his tiny Stand. When push comes to shove, Polnareff resorts to the unthinkable.
episodes.title: Set's Alessi, Part 2

episodes.synopsis: Jotaro and his crew finally arrive in Cairo. They meet a man at a café who claims to know where DIO’s mansion is, but he refuses to talk for free.
episodes.title: D'Arby the Gambler, Part 1

episodes.synopsis: Jotaro demonstrates his Stand’s abilities as a warning against cheating before starting a game of poker against Stand user D’Arby.
episodes.title: D'Arby the Gambler, Part 2

episodes.synopsis: Hol Horse arrives at the airport in Cairo under orders to kill Jotaro and his crew; inside his suitcase lies his new unwilling partner.
episodes.title: Hol Horse and Boingo, Part 1

episodes.synopsis: Hol Horse acts according to the prophecy in the book, but he starts to have doubts when Jotaro and the rest of his crew show up at the scene.
episodes.title: Hol Horse and Boingo, Part 2

episodes.synopsis: Avdol searches for information on DIO’s mansion in Cairo. Meanwhile, Iggy gets confronted by two big, menacing dogs while taking a walk in the city.
episodes.title: The Guardian of Hell, Pet Shop, Part 1

episodes.synopsis: Iggy escapes into the river after being seriously wounded in a battle against the falcon Stand user Pet Shop, but Pet Shop shows no sign of giving up.
episodes.title: The Guardian of Hell, Pet Shop, Part 2

episodes.synopsis: Jotaro and his crew are greeted at the door of DIO’s mansion by a butler named D’Arby, who claims to be the younger brother of D’Arby the Gambler.
episodes.title: D'Arby the Player, Part 1

episodes.synopsis: Kakyoin loses his soul in a racing game against D’Arby. Jotaro berates Joseph as he goes up next and selects a game the butler is best at.
episodes.title: D'Arby the Player, Part 2

episodes.synopsis: While D’Arby finds Jotaro’s pitching announcements strange, he remains confident due to his Stand. Meanwhile, Avdol and the others enter the mansion.
episodes.title: The Miasma of the Void, Vanilla Ice, Part 1

episodes.synopsis: Polnareff and Iggy quickly press forward to destroy DIO, but the vicious vampire Vanilla Ice comes up from behind to take them both out.
episodes.title: The Miasma of the Void, Vanilla Ice, Part 2

episodes.synopsis: The mortally-wounded Iggy musters the last of his strength to save Polnareff. Finally, Polnareff stabs Vanilla Ice in the head.
episodes.title: The Miasma of the Void, Vanilla Ice, Part 3

episodes.synopsis: Polnareff faces DIO at last, but is unable to get close for some unknown reason; he unleashes his Silver Chariot to reveal DIO’s Stand.
episodes.title: Dio's World, Part 1

episodes.synopsis: Kakyoin sets up barriers in order to unmask the identity of DIO’s Stand. Hierophant Green targets DIO with concentrated fire as he falls for his trap.
episodes.title: Dio's World, Part 2

episodes.synopsis: DIO uses his Stand’s ability to stop time. Just as he moves in for the kill, he notices that Jotaro’s fingers are moving despite being frozen in time.
episodes.title: Dio's World, Part 3

episodes.synopsis: DIO stands before Joseph’s bloodless body. An enraged Jotaro confronts the fully healed DIO for a final battle in the world of frozen time.
episodes.title: Long Journey Farewell, My Friends

episodes.synopsis: Jotaro Kujo goes to the town of Morioh to find Josuke Higashikata. He sees someone who turns out to be Josuke vehemently apologizing to some bullies.
episodes.title: Jotaro Kujo! Meets Josuke Higashikata

episodes.synopsis: Angelo’s Stand can somehow enter people’s bodies. Just after Jotaro warns him not to consume anything, Josuke catches his mom taking a sip of coffee.
episodes.title: Josuke Higashikata! Meets Angelo

episodes.synopsis: In order to keep the town from harm’s way, Jotaro goes on a search to destroy the mysterious bow and arrow that awakened Angelo’s Stand abilities.
episodes.title: The Nijimura Brothers, Part 1

episodes.synopsis: Trying to save Koichi, Josuke goes to Okuyasu Nijimura’s house, but gets attacked by his brother, Keicho. Josuke offers the injured Okuyasu a deal.
episodes.title: The Nijimura Brothers, Part 2

episodes.synopsis: Josuke and Koichi decide to find and destroy the bow and arrow to prevent more victims. They find it in the attic but hear an eerie sound from within.
episodes.title: The Nijimura Brothers, Part 3

episodes.synopsis: Koichi runs over a cat in a bag while riding his bike to school. A man sees it happen and tries to blackmail Koichi into paying for the cat’s burial.
episodes.title: Koichi Hirose (Reverb)

episodes.synopsis: Josuke and Koichi investigate to see if their schoolmate Toshikazu Hazamada is really using a Stand and find a wooden dummy in his locker.
episodes.title: Toshikazu Hazamada (Show Off)

episodes.synopsis: Koichi’s classmate Yukako Yamagishi confesses her love for him. He is overjoyed, but her love is scarily abnormal and eventually goes too far.
episodes.title: Yukako Yamagishi Falls in Love, Part 1

episodes.synopsis: Koichi tries to escape but is foiled by Yukako and loses hope. When she goes to a payphone outside the villa, something unexpected happens!
episodes.title: Yukako Yamagishi Falls in Love, Part 2

episodes.synopsis: Josuke and Okuyasu go to a new Italian restaurant that is a little strange. Okuyasu thinks the water is delicious but his body has a strange reaction.
episodes.title: Let's Go Eat Some Italian Food

episodes.synopsis: Red Hot Chili Pepper, who has killed Keicho and stolen the bow and arrow, appears before Josuke. Jotaro tells Josuke and the other two about a guy.
episodes.title: Chili Pepper, Part 1

episodes.synopsis: Following Jotaro’s orders, Josuke and Koichi stay on the docks and watch for Chili Pepper. The Stand’s user appears, confident he can beat them.
episodes.title: Chili Pepper, Part 2

episodes.synopsis: As Josuke reluctantly tries to get his father Joseph to head back home, the old man causes all kinds of trouble, then says a Stand user is nearby.
episodes.title: We Picked Up Something Crazy!

episodes.synopsis: Koichi and Hazamada are excited to visit the home of popular manga artist, Rohan Kishibe. But they soon get spooked out by him.
episodes.title: Let's Go to the Manga Artist's House, Part 1

episodes.synopsis: Rohan says Koichi is inspiring him to create his manga. Just when he is about to turn Koichi into more manga material, someone comes to the door.
episodes.title: Let's Go to the Manga Artist's House, Part 2

episodes.synopsis: Jotaro enlists Josuke to hunt a rat that has Stand powers. At the irrigation canal where the rat was caught on tape, they encounter a bizarre sight.
episodes.title: Let's Go Hunting!

episodes.synopsis: Koichi and Rohan find something strange in an alley not marked on the town map. Sensing even more disturbance, Rohan thinks it is a Stand attack.
episodes.title: Rohan Kishibe's Adventure

episodes.synopsis: Josuke and Okuyasu spot a bunch of tiny Stands picking up coins on the street and chase them back to a kid named Shigechi. Josuke gets an idea.
episodes.title: Shigechi's Harvest, Part 1

episodes.synopsis: Josuke, Okuyasu and Shigechi go to the bank to collect their lottery reward. The banker aims to prove it is not their ticket, so Josuke takes action.
episodes.title: Shigechi's Harvest, Part 2

episodes.synopsis: Yukako sees an esthetician to get her face done with “Makeup to Encounter Love” to turn Koichi’s head. It works, but the effect only lasts 30 minutes.
episodes.title: Yukako Yamagishi Dreams of Cinderella

episodes.synopsis: Shigechi mistakenly takes the lunch bag of Yoshikage Kira, who pursues Shigechi to get it back before he discovers his vile secret hiding inside.
episodes.title: Yoshikage Kira Just Wants to Live Quietly, Part 1

episodes.synopsis: Shigechi manages to escape from Kira. Severely injured, he tries to reach Josuke to get healed and warn him of the threat that Kira poses.
episodes.title: Yoshikage Kira Just Wants to Live Quietly, Part 2

episodes.synopsis: Jotaro warns Koichi to be extra cautious and stops him from pursuing Kira. Koichi lets his guard down and the next moment the bomb Stand attacks him.
episodes.title: Heart Attack, Part 1

episodes.synopsis: Kira the serial killer appears and Koichi is enraged. Kira is still furious about being humiliated in public and proceeds to beat Koichi to a pulp.
episodes.title: Heart Attack, Part 2

episodes.synopsis: Josuke and Jotaro search the house that Kira once lived in. They find a boring man’s odd hobby. Then, a Polaroid camera on a desk takes their picture.
episodes.title: Heart Father

episodes.synopsis: Yoshihiro Kira searches for Stand users who will help protect his son. Meanwhile, a boy asks Rohan, who is pursuing Kira, to play rock-paper-scissors.
episodes.title: Janken Boy is Coming!

episodes.synopsis: Kira lives as Kosaku Kawajiri, but gets the urge to kill upon seeing his wife’s neck. Meanwhile, Josuke and Okuyasu find a strange man in a field.
episodes.title: I'm an Alien

episodes.synopsis: Rohan suspects Josuke is cheating at dice and bets two million yen that he can figure out how. Josuke will lose a pinky if Rohan wins the next round.
episodes.title: Highway Go Go, Part 1

episodes.synopsis: Josuke is being chased by a Stand and will get caught if he goes below 60 kmph on his bike. He nabs a cellphone to call Koichi but isn’t safe yet!
episodes.title: Highway Go Go, Part 2

episodes.synopsis: Kawajiri goes into the basement to confront a cat with a hole in its throat, but finds it dead. The next day a strange plant grows on the cat’s grave.
episodes.title: Cats Love Yoshikage Kira

episodes.synopsis: Yoshihiro, certain Kosaku Kawajiri is his son, takes action to protect him from Jotaro. Josuke and Okuyasu find a man living on an electrical pylon.
episodes.title: July 15th (Thurs), Part 1

episodes.synopsis: An eccentric architect named Masazo Kinoto visits Rohan to inspect the fire-damaged house. Josuke and Kanedaichi battle on the pylon.
episodes.title: July 15th (Thurs), Part 2

episodes.synopsis: Rohan is in trouble after seeing Kinoto’s back. Meanwhile, a young man appears before Josuke and takes out a folded paper that is hiding something.
episodes.title: July 15th (Thurs), Part 3

episodes.synopsis: Rohan calls Koichi for help as he can’t expose his back, but Koichi doesn’t believe him. Risking showing his back, Rohan heads for Jotaro’s hotel.
episodes.title: July 15th (Thurs), Part 4

episodes.synopsis: Kosaku Kawajiri finally kills Hayato. Learning of Hayato, Rohan and the others go to check Kosaku Kawajiri’s house.
episodes.title: Bites the Dust, Part 1

episodes.synopsis: Hayato sees that anyone who learns about Yoshikage Kira through him gets blown away, after which the same morning repeats.
episodes.title: Bites the Dust, Part 2

episodes.synopsis: Kira aims to undo the third power, Bite The Dust, as Hayato blew up several people and returned to the same morning. But someone appears before Kira.
episodes.title: Shining D (Diamond) is Unbreakable, Part 1

episodes.synopsis: An air bomb passes through the walls into a house where Josuke and Hayato are hiding. The two don’t know how the bomb can see Josuke from outside.
episodes.title: Shining D (Diamond) is Unbreakable, Part 2

episodes.synopsis: Even cornered, Kira won’t give up. He puts Bites The Dust on a rescue worker and tries to blow away time by pressing his Stand Killer Queen’s switch.
episodes.title: Goodbye, Morioh – The Heart of Gold

episodes.synopsis: With his Stand most suitable for the task, Koichi Hirose arrives in Naples to locate young Haruno Shiobana, a man feared to be Dio Brando’s son.
episodes.title: Golden Wind

episodes.synopsis: As a neglected child, Giorno’s life changes when he helps a mafioso escape death. Giorno learns more about his powers while facing Bruno Bucciarati.
episodes.title: Bucciarati Is Coming

episodes.synopsis: Determined to join the mafia group known as Passione, Giorno visits ranking member Polpo in prison, where he's given an impossible test of initiation.
episodes.title: Meet the Gangster Behind the Wall

episodes.synopsis: Giorno struggles against Polpo's Stand, who can maneuver freely between the shadows. Koichi tells Giorno of a stand-manifesting arrow.
episodes.title: Gang Initiation

episodes.synopsis: As news of Polpo’s hidden stash spreads through the ranks of Passione, Bucciarati and his gang set sail to retrieve it for themselves.
episodes.title: Find Polpo's Fortune!

episodes.synopsis: With Bucciarati's crew mysteriously disappearing below deck, Abbacchio initiates his Stand, Moody Jazz, to investigate the disturbing phenomenon.
episodes.title: Moody Jazz's Counterattack

episodes.synopsis: The gang learns of a threat awaiting their arrival on Capri. With Giorno, Mista proceeds to neutralize the enemy with his Stands, the Six Bullets.
episodes.title: Six Bullets Appears Part 1

episodes.synopsis: Mista is lured aboard a moving truck where Sale's Stand, Arts and Crafts, displays the ability to control muzzle energy from the Six Bullet's bullets.
episodes.title: Six Bullets Appears Part 2

episodes.synopsis: With Polpo's hidden stash of priceless gems delivered, Passione caporegime Pericolo promotes Bucciarati to a ranking member inside the organization.
episodes.title: The First Mission From the Boss

episodes.synopsis: While out on a supply run, Narancia is intercepted by Hitman Team member Formaggio, who shrinks the underling down using the powers of Tiny Feet.
episodes.title: Hitman Team

episodes.synopsis: An ever-shrinking Narancia scrambles to stay alive as Formaggio continues to press him for the whereabouts of the boss’s daughter.
episodes.title: Narancia's Li'l Bomber

episodes.synopsis: Bucciarati sends Giorno and his men to the ruins of Pompeii, where a run-in with Illuso gets Fugo trapped in a mirror world without his Stand.
episodes.title: The Second Mission From the Boss

episodes.synopsis: Abbacchio proceeds to retrieve the key necessary to transfer the boss's daughter to safety, but first he must face Illuso inside the mirror world.
episodes.title: Mirror Man and Purple Smoke

episodes.synopsis: Bucciarati’s crew have orders to board a Florence-bound express train, but they can’t figure out how to use their key, and the hitmen are closing in.
episodes.title: Express Train to Florence

episodes.synopsis: With Bucciarati's crew rapidly aging from an unknown attack, Mista comes out of hiding to investigate but is quickly ensnared by the Beach Boy Stand.
episodes.title: Thankful Death Part 1

episodes.synopsis: Moved by the dying Prosciutto’s sheer determination to keep his Thankful Death Stand activated, Pesci resolves to take on Bucciarati.
episodes.title: Thankful Death Part 2

episodes.synopsis: Merone uses an inadvertent young woman’s body to spawn a Stand that he sends in pursuit of Trish, who shows signs of being a Stand-user herself.
episodes.title: Babyhead

episodes.synopsis: With Babyhead attempting to dice him into cubes through matter-manipulation, Giorno wields Golden Wind's life-generating powers and fights back.
episodes.title: Head to Venice!

episodes.synopsis: Giorno and Mista arrive in Venice to retrieve the data disk, but Ghiaccio’s White Ice! Stand thwarts their mission by freezing everything in sight.
episodes.title: White Ice

episodes.synopsis: Bucciarati escorts Trish up the bell tower to finally deliver her to her father, but a devastating betrayal jeopardizes both of their lives.
episodes.title: The Final Mission From the Boss

episodes.synopsis: Realizing he'd been duped, Bucciarati resolves to defeat his double-crossing boss and save Trish, but Emperor Crimson continues to have the upper hand.
episodes.title: The Mystery of Emperor Crimson

episodes.synopsis: Now traitors to Passione, Bucciarati's crew must figure out their next move, but getting away from the boss won't be easy.
episodes.title: The "G" in Guts

episodes.synopsis: With Giorno incapacitated from Squalo's attack, Narancia uses his Aerosmith Stand's radar ability to seek and destroy the oncoming threat.
episodes.title: Crush and Talking Mouth

episodes.synopsis: Bucciarati and crew prepare to leave for Sardinia to uncover their boss's past, but a strange Stand-user appears before they can take off.
episodes.title: Notorious Chase

episodes.synopsis: Alone in the cabin and under attack, Trish is suddenly aided by a strange being calling itself Spicy Lady -- a Stand of her very own.
episodes.title: Spicy Lady

episodes.synopsis: While on a mission to track down Trish in Sardinia for the boss, loyal subordinate Doppio encounters the traitorous Risotto.
episodes.title: A Little Story From the Past ~My Name Is Doppio~

episodes.synopsis: Deducing that Doppio is more than just an associate of Passione, Risotto methodically attacks him with the magnetic ability of his Stand, Metallic.
episodes.title: Emperor Crimson vs. Metallic

episodes.synopsis: Determined to identify their boss, Abbacchio activates his Stand to reveal the photographer who took the picture of Trish’s mother 15 years ago.
episodes.title: Under a Sky That Could Come Falling at Any Moment

episodes.synopsis: When Bucciarati and crew receive an anonymous call about their boss's identity and how to defeat him, they head to Rome to meet the caller.
episodes.title: Get to the Collessium in Rome!

episodes.synopsis: To flee from Cioccolata’s flesh-eating Stand, Green Tea, Bucciarati and Mista try to find a getaway car, but Secco's determined to stop their escape.
episodes.title: Green Tea and Sanctuary Part 1

episodes.synopsis: Cioccolata attempts to wipe out innocent civilians with his Stand via helicopter, but Giorno and Mista seek to take him down first.
episodes.title: Green Tea and Sanctuary Part 2

episodes.synopsis: To stop Secco from getting to the Colosseum first, Bucciarati pulls him into a duel beneath the streets of Rome.
episodes.title: Green Tea and Sanctuary Part 3

episodes.synopsis: Too injured to realize who's helping him, Bucciarati is led to the Colosseum by Doppio, who reveals his true identity to the person waiting inside.
episodes.title: His Name Is Diavolo

episodes.synopsis: As Emperor Crimson is unleashed on Polnareff, Silver Chariot is pierced with the Arrow. Those inside the Colosseum then fall into a mysterious sleep.
episodes.title: The Requiem Quietly Plays Part 1

episodes.synopsis: With everyone’s souls swapped out with each others', Mista and the others must somehow retrieve the Arrow before Diavolo takes it for himself.
episodes.title: The Requiem Quietly Plays Part 2

episodes.synopsis: While Silver Chariot Requiem causes the entities around it to mutate, Giorno deduces that Diavolo’s soul must be possessing one of his crew.
episodes.title: Diavolo Surfaces

episodes.synopsis: Despite their best efforts, the Arrow falls into Diavolo's hands. But just before the boss can pierce his own Stand with it, Bucciarati makes a move.
episodes.title: King of Kings

episodes.synopsis: Giorno's Stand evolves into Golden Wind Requiem. Diavolo tries to nullify his attacks, but a horrifying new reality awaits the mob boss.
episodes.title: Golden Wind Requiem

episodes.synopsis: While investigating the mystery of the florist's daughter's suspicious suicide, Mista comes face to face with a Stand-user named Scolippi.
episodes.title: The Sleep Slave

episodes.synopsis: Florida, 2011. Framed for a DUI and imprisoned, young Jolyne gains a mysterious new power after receiving a bizarre item from her estranged father.
episodes.title: Stone Ocean

episodes.synopsis: Jolyne gets acquainted with Green Dolphin Street Prison and her two-faced cellmate, Gwess, who has obtained Jolyne's locket and a pint-sized new Stand.
episodes.title: Prisoner FE40536: Jolyne Cujoh

episodes.synopsis: Jolyne acclimates to prison, but a mysterious boy delivers an ominous message before Jolyne receives a visit from her father and an enemy Stand user.
episodes.title: The Visitor (1)

episodes.synopsis: DIO's follower Johngalli A. aims for revenge. The boy risks his safety to help Jotaro and Jolyne, but she refuses to leave the kid behind.
episodes.title: The Visitor (2)

episodes.synopsis: Father and daughter try to escape the visiting room's trap and the prison, but an enemy Stand extracts two discs from Jotaro. One holds Star Platinum.
episodes.title: Prisoner of Love

episodes.synopsis: Jolyne returns to prison to retrieve Jotaro's discs. Ermes Costello discovers her new ability and a guard with discs in his head before she's attacked.
episodes.title: Ermes’s Stickers

episodes.synopsis: After people go missing from the prison's farm, Jolyne and Ermes volunteer to join the search party as a way to look for Pale Snake and the discs.
episodes.title: There’s Six of Us!

episodes.synopsis: Jolyne and Ermes unravel the mystery of Stand F.F. and its user, who admits to helping Pale Snake in his efforts to steal their Stands.
episodes.title: F.F.

episodes.synopsis: Pale Snake's user, Father Pucchi, makes his entrance. A baseball game in the yard against Miraschon heats up when F.F. and Stone Ocean get involved.
episodes.title: Debt Collector Mary Lynn Manson

episodes.synopsis: Assisted by Emporio and his friend Weather Forecast, Jolyne rushes to the courtyard to pass Jotaro's Stand Disc to the Speedwagon Foundation.
episodes.title: Operation Savage Guardian (Head to the Courtyard!) (1)

episodes.synopsis: Father Pucchi learns some damning information. Jolyne and Weather's bodies strain under Jumpin' Jack Spark's Stand ability as the fight continues.
episodes.title: Operation Savage Guardian (Head to the Courtyard!) (2)

episodes.synopsis: Jolyne reaches the courtyard. Pucchi recalls his talks with DIO and his reason for hunting Jotaro when Weather unleashes a squall of poison dart frogs.
episodes.title: Torrential Downpour Warning
